			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1881986">
									

<p>While I balked at 1716 giving Dark a face, I like the approach this takes. It's &quot;Here's what we know&quot;, which is practically nothing, and &quot;Here's what we know we don't know&quot;, which is everything else. Even with that last segment from the Library (as an aside, the Library stuff still doesn't do much for me and feels a bit self-indulgent as a consequence, but you've at least prefaced it acceptably), it's &quot;this information is quite likely wrong, but it's all we've got&quot;, and despite the fears stated above, I daresay this leaves open a lot of room for creativity on behalf of others.</p>

